notesStmt.note: 1. p.1-199: Commentarii in octo libros Aristotelis de physico auditu -- 2. p.200-280: Disputationes in libros Aristotelis de mundo, caelo et elementis -- 3. p.282-287: Index eorum quae in prima huius libri parte continentur -- 4. p.1-56: In libros Aristotelis de ortu et interitu -- 5. p.57-131: Disputationes in tres Aristotelis libros de anima -- 6. p.132-147: Disputatio unica in metaphysicam -- 7. p.150-188: Disputationes de philosophia morali -- 8. p.190-193: In theses sex metaphysicae et moraliae.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Lecture notes on multiple works of Aristotle, including the Physics, De caelo, De generatione et corruptione, De anima, and Metaphysics, written by a student in Bordeaux in 1643 and 1644.

msItem.title: Commentarii in octo libros Aristotelis de physico auditu
Disputationes in libros Aristotelis de mundo, caelo et elementis
Index eorum quae in prima huius libri parte continentur
In libros Aristotelis de ortu et interitu
Disputationes in tres Aristotelis libros de anima
In theses sex metaphysicae et moraliae

support.watermark: Initials RM enclosed in an circle with a trefoil above and an upside-down heart below.

supportDesc.extent: 243 leaves : 235 x 171 (191 x 133) mm bound to 241 x 179 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 234 leaves; [Part 1] [i-vi], 1-75, 77-146, [i-ii], 147-284, [285-287], [Part 2] 1-50, 52-188, [189-193]; contemporary pagination in ink, modern pagination in pencil, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Small diagram, Arc of circle transecting a square

binding.p: Contemporary (17th-century) sheep (Addison & Sarova) with minimal gilt on covers and spine.

origin.p: Written in Bordeaux (Burdigalae in manuscript), 1643-1644 (title page, p. iii; Part 2, p. 147).

history.provenance: Student ownership inscriptions, including Chauseyr (p. i, v) and Laurentius Leonardus Mazeau Desgranges (p. i, v-vi, 1, and possibly the same hand writing "L'an mil sept cent," p. 281),
Sold by Addison & Sarova Auctioneers (Macon, Georgia), 5 November 2016, lot 130.
